

The Boston Family Office | Investment Services



































































   



















The Boston Family Office was founded in 1996 by professionals responsible for the financial affairs of their families as well as other individuals and trusts.  After decades of experience, they felt that they could achieve better results and service in a smaller, independent firm.	

The Boston Family Office now manages over $1 billion in assets, spread over more than 175 individuals and families, each individually managed by a principal of the firm. 



The Boston Family Office | 88 Broad Street Boston, MA 02110617.624.0800 | 800.900.4401


































The Boston Family Office | People | Michael Unger, CFA























































































































Michael J. Unger, CFA is a partner of and portfolio manager at The Boston Family Office.  He joined the firm in 2000.


Previously, Michael headed the investment management team for Mellon Private Capital Management's Charitable Giving service, a new line of business at the time that he joined Mellon.  Prior to that, he managed individual and institutional investment portfolios for Key Trust Company of Ohio/Key Asset Management. 


He graduated in 1990 from the University of Dayton with a BS in Finance and with a minor in History. His interests include running, motorcycles, and sailing. 


Michael was born and grew up in Southern Africa, spending his childhood in Malawi, South Africa, and what is now Zimbabwe.   After living near Boston for many years, he now telecommutes from Boulder, Colorado where he lives with his wife Jean.

