Boston Family Office LLC Has $569,000 Stake in Emerson Electric Company (NYSE:EMR)

Posted by Toi Williams on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments 

Boston Family Office LLC cut its position in shares of Emerson Electric Company (NYSE:EMR) by 0.5% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 9,506 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 50 shares during the period. Boston Family Office LLC’s holdings in Emerson Electric were worth $569,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Other hedge funds also recently modified their holdings of the company. Northwest Quadrant Wealth Management LLC acquired a new position in Emerson Electric during the fourth quarter worth approximately $111,000. First Command Financial Services Inc. boosted its stake in shares of Emerson Electric by 18.9% in the first quarter. First Command Financial Services Inc. now owns 1,935 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $116,000 after buying an additional 307 shares during the period. Central Bank & Trust Co. boosted its stake in shares of Emerson Electric by 31.3% in the first quarter. Central Bank & Trust Co. now owns 2,100 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $126,000 after buying an additional 500 shares during the period. Ancora Advisors LLC purchased a new stake in shares of Emerson Electric during the fourth quarter worth about $158,000. Finally, Independent Advisor Alliance purchased a new stake in shares of Emerson Electric during the fourth quarter worth about $194,000. 68.87% of the stock is owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 




Emerson Electric Company (EMR) opened at 60.30 on Friday. The company has a market cap of $38.86 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 25.76 and a beta of 1.20. Emerson Electric Company has a 52 week low of $49.22 and a 52 week high of $64.36. The firm has a 50-day moving average of $59.68 and a 200-day moving average of $59.54. 


 Get Emerson Electric Company alerts:



Emerson Electric (NYSE:EMR) last posted its earnings results on Tuesday, May 2nd. The industrial products company reported $0.58 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, meeting the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.58. Emerson Electric had a return on equity of 23.37% and a net margin of 8.72%. The firm had revenue of $3.57 billion for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $3.49 billion. During the same period in the previous year, the firm earned $0.57 earnings per share. The business’s revenue was down .1% compared to the same quarter last year. Equities analysts forecast that Emerson Electric Company will post $2.60 earnings per share for the current year. 
